The number of new cases of coronary pneumonia outside China has increased 13-fold

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
World Health Organization (WHO) director-general Tan Desai declared that the new crown epidemic can be assessed as a "pandemic. ". (photo: World Health Organization's official twitter feed)

On March 11, Central European time, World Health Organization (WHO) director-general Tan Desai announced that the new crown epidemic can be assessed as a "pandemic. ". He said the number of new cases of pneumonia outside China had increased 13-fold in the past two weeks, and he was deeply concerned about "worrying inaction. ".

"The announcement of the pandemic confirms what weeks of data have shown: that the new coronavirus is spreading in many countries around the world. This does not mean the situation is worse today than it was yesterday, but it is just a warning that every country needs to be ready for a new crown of prevention,"said Fei Heping, former director of the CDC.

The last time World Health Organization declared a pandemic was in 2009 with a new influenza virus, H1N1, known as "swine flu, " which had been circulating in several countries for about six weeks. It is now a seasonal, regular flu. After the outbreak began to spread internationally, World Health Organization's Emergency Committee on January 30 characterized it as a "public health emergency of international concern. ".

There are 118,000 new cases of pneumonia in 114 countries / regions, with more than 90% of the cases concentrated in four countries / regions, with two of them (China and South Korea) showing significant declines, the WHO said in a March 11 press release. No cases have been reported in 81 countries and 10 or fewer cases have been reported in 57 countries.

As of 17:00 Beijing Time on March 11, a total of 37,371 cases of new coronary pneumonia and 1,130 deaths had been confirmed in 113 countries and regions outside China. Compared with the previous day's data, 4,596 new cases and 258 new deaths were confirmed outside China. Four new countries and territories -- Florida, Jamaica, Burkina Faso, Democratic Republic of Congo.

"This is the first time that a coronavirus infection has been described as a pandemic, but at the same time, we believe it will be the first outbreak that can be contained, " Tan said, several countries have demonstrated that the virus can be suppressed and controlled. He called on governments to take "urgent and positive action" to change the course of the epidemic.

In fact, past coronavirus infections such as SARS (as) and Mers (Middle East Respiratory Syndrome) were not defined as global pandemics.

Zhang Zuofeng, associate dean of the Public Health Department at the University of California, Los Angeles, and a senior tenured professor of epidemiology, told China Newsweek that World Health Organization's "pandemic" was announced too late, this is because cases of NCP have been reported on six continents and are characterized by high human-to-human transmission and mortality. "after the declaration of a pandemic, governments have made the prevention and control of the epidemic a top priority, and the WHO has a responsibility to work with all countries to mobilize heads of government and relevant agencies to control the epidemic. "

It's not too late, but it could have been announced earlier, public health professor Gao Benen told China Newsweek. As early as early February, it became clear that it would be extremely difficult to contain the epidemic and prevent it from becoming a global pandemic.

Marc Lipsitch, Professor of epidemiology statistics at the Harvard School of Public Health and Director of the Center for the dynamics of infectious diseases, used computational models to predict on March 3 that 20 to 60 percent of the world's adults would be infected with the new coronavirus. However, he explained that this worrying prediction would only come about in the absence of a strong response. If countries continue with interventions such as the cancellation of public gatherings and school closures, the epidemic may slow down or stop before it reaches this level of infection.

The epidemic situation in China has entered a stable period. On March 11, there were 15 newly confirmed cases, and a total of 80,793 confirmed cases were reported. The situation in Italy is serious, the number of cases is increasing rapidly and there is a risk of a run on medical resources, Zhang told China news weekly. To make matters worse, the epidemic began to spread from northern Italy to the south, where economic capacity and health-care systems were much weaker than in the north. Hours after the WHO announcement, Italy announced Europe's toughest blockade yet.

Zhang style pointed out that the problem with Iran is that the actual situation is not clear, the opposition parties have come forward to say that the actual number of people infected and killed is much higher than the official figures, and that Iran has been under international sanctions for some time, the economy and health care system are relatively weak, the future is likely to be a more serious disaster area. South Korea, by contrast, is determined to test 10,000 people a day for early detection, isolation and close contact, and the number of infections is now declining.

In the United States, the most questionable aspect of outbreak control is testing. At the latest count, 1,311 people have been infected in the United States, making it the eighth-largest country in the world for the number of cases. But Marc Lipsitch, Professor of epidemiology statistics at the Harvard School of Public Health, said the new cases being reported each day were not "new" but new findings as the number of people tested increased. He believes that the U. S. detection capacity is far from enough, and the actual number of infections far higher. At an 11-day hearing in the U.S. House of Representatives, CDC Director Robert Redfield said there are some deaths from the new coronavirus that were previously diagnosed as flu.

The NBA suspended all games for the rest of the season after Tom Hanks and his wife tested positive for a new coronavirus in Australia on March 12, Beijing time. On the evening of March 11 local time, US President Donald Trump announced that European tourists (except the UK) would be banned from travelling to the US for the next 30 days, starting at midnight on Friday, March 13, in an effort to control the epidemic. A subsequent presidential announcement made it clear that tourists from 26 countries in Schengen Area would be barred from entering the country.

Border restrictions are an important tool, but when community transmission occurs, a set of measures to reduce the risk of infection in the community is needed, Zhang said.
